# ROLE
You are a senior frontend engineer and static-site architect.
Generate production-ready code based strictly on the requirements below.
Prefer clarity, simplicity, and static generation.

---

# GOAL
Build a **technical blog static website** similar to hoclaptrinh.io
using **Static Site Generation**.

The site must be optimized for:
- SEO
- Performance
- Markdown-based content
- Zero monthly hosting cost

---

# TECH STACK CONSTRAINTS
- Framework: **Next.js (Static Generation)**
  - Use App Router if possible
  - No server-side runtime features
- Styling: **Tailwind CSS**
- Content format: **Markdown (.md or .mdx)**
- Code highlighting: **PrismJS or Shiki**
- Deployment target: **Vercel / Netlify**
- No backend, no database

---

# CORE FEATURES (MUST IMPLEMENT)

## 1. Homepage
- List latest articles sorted by date (descending)
- Each article preview shows:
  - Title
  - Description
  - Publish date
  - Category
- Fully static
- Responsive layout

## 2. Article Page
- Render Markdown/MDX content
- Support:
  - Headings (H1–H4)
  - Tables
  - Images
  - Inline code
  - Code blocks
- Syntax highlighting for:
  - SQL
  - JavaScript
  - Bash
- Clean reading layout similar to technical blogs

## 3. Table of Contents (TOC)
- Auto-generate TOC from H2/H3 headings
- TOC displayed on article page
- Anchor links scroll smoothly

## 4. Categories
- Each article belongs to exactly one category
- Category pages:
  - `/category/[slug]`
  - List all articles in that category
- Pages must be statically generated

## 5. SEO
- Clean URLs:
  `/articles/[slug]`
- Meta tags:
  - title
  - description
  - OpenGraph tags
- Generate:
  - sitemap.xml
  - robots.txt
- Lighthouse SEO score target ≥ 90

## 6. Navigation
- Header:
  - Home
  - Categories
  - About
- Footer:
  - Copyright
  - External Buy Me a Coffee link

---

# CONTENT MODEL

## Article Frontmatter (REQUIRED)
```yaml
title: "SQL INSERT Statement"
description: "Learn how to use INSERT in SQL with examples"
date: "2026-02-05"
category: "SQL"
slug: "sql-insert-statement"